
apply()
=======

The apply method is similar to call, but it takes an array-like object of arguements instead of individual arguements.

Syntax
-------

function.apply(thisArg, [arg1, arg2, ...])


Example
------
const person = {
    fullName: function ( location, rollNo) {
        return `${this.firstName} ${this.lastName} from ${location}, RollNo ${rollNo}`
    }
};

const person1 = {
    firstName: "Arjun",
    lastName: "Doss"
};

const person2 = {
    firstName: "Kamal",
    lastName: "Hassan"
};


console.log(person.fullName.apply(person1, ["Bangalore", 34])) // Arjun Doss from Bangalore, RollNO 34
console.log(person.fullName.apply(person2, ["Chennai", 30])) // Kamal Hassan from Chennai, RollNo 30

